CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1773867709
OL,3,CTaoiseach defends the Prime Minister
OL,4,Cfrom Trump's criticism at the White
OL,5,CHouse
OL,7,FTaoiseach Micheal Martin has stepped
OL,8,Fin to defend Prime Minister Sir Keir
OL,9,FStarmer from criticism from President
OL,10,FDonald Trump during their joint press
OL,11,Fconference in the Oval Office to mark
OL,12,FSt Patrick's Day.
OL,14,FThe US President hit out at the Prime
OL,15,FMinister for not giving more support
OL,16,Fto America in the war in the Middle
OL,17,FEast.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1773867709
OL,3,CTaoiseach defends the Prime Minister
OL,4,Cfrom Trump's criticism at the White
OL,5,CHouse
OL,7,FThe meeting began with a discussion
OL,8,Fabout the relationship between Ireland
OL,9,Fand the US, however during a press
OL,10,Fconference attention turned to the war
OL,11,Fin Iran, NATO and the Prime Minister.
OL,13,FThe president has called on allied
OL,14,Fnations to provide vessels to help
OL,15,Fopen the Strait of Hormuz and has
OL,16,Fcriticised Sir Keir Starmer for so far
OL,17,Fdeclining to commit the Royal Navy.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1773867709
OL,3,CTaoiseach defends the Prime Minister
OL,4,Cfrom Trump's criticism at the White
OL,5,CHouse
OL,7,FMr Trump said he "liked" the Prime
OL,8,FMinister but felt "disappointed" with
OL,9,Fhis recent position in regard to the
OL,10,Fconflict with Iran.
OL,12,FHe also described Sir Keir's policies
OL,13,Fon both immigration and energy as a
OL,14,F"disaster".
OL,16,FThe president was asked by reporters
OL,17,Fin the Oval Office whether his
OL,18,Frelationship with Sir Keir has been
OL,19,Fdamaged by the UK's stance over the
OL,20,Fwar in Iran.
OL,26,@oD@ROUoD@XO]pD@SOUpD@`O]vD@AOUvD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1773867709
OL,3,CTaoiseach defends the Prime Minister
OL,4,Cfrom Trump's criticism at the White
OL,5,CHouse
OL,7,F"I was disappointed, because Keir was
OL,8,Fwilling to send two aircraft carriers
OL,9,Fafter we won, because essentially...
OL,10,Fthere's no threat for the aircraft
OL,11,Fcarriers right now.
OL,13,F"And I said, 'no, no, we want things
OL,14,Fsent before the war, not after the war
OL,15,Fis won'.
OL,17,F"So, yeah, I'm disappointed with Keir.
OL,18,FI like him, I think he's a nice man,
OL,19,Fbut I'm disappointed."
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@AOUyD@AOU{D@VO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1773867709
OL,3,CTaoiseach defends the Prime Minister
OL,4,Cfrom Trump's criticism at the White
OL,5,CHouse
OL,7,FMr Trump then repeated his assertion
OL,8,Fthat "unfortunately Keir is no Winston
OL,9,FChurchill".
OL,11,FThe US president hosted the Taoiseach
OL,12,Fin the White House on St Patrick's
OL,13,FDay, the culmination of days of US-
OL,14,FIrish engagements organised each year.
OL,16,FThe 40-minute meeting also involved Mr
OL,17,FTrump responding to Irish president
OL,18,FCatherine Connolly's criticism of US-
OL,19,FIsraeli attacks on Iran by saying the
OL,20,Fworld "should be thankful" for the
OL,21,Fintervention.
OL,26,@pD@FOUqD@JO]|D@GOU|D@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1773867709
OL,3,CTaoiseach defends the Prime Minister
OL,4,Cfrom Trump's criticism at the White
OL,5,CHouse
OL,7,FHe also doubled down on his previous
OL,8,Fcriticisms of Nato and accused Prime
OL,9,FMinister Sir Keir Starmer of making a
OL,10,F"big mistake" on Iran.
OL,12,FMr Martin defended Sir Keir by telling
OL,13,FMr Trump he "had the capacity" to
OL,14,Fengage with the British leader and
OL,15,Fother European leaders.
OL,26,@rD@AOUrD@MO]uD@MOUuD@^O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1773867709
OL,3,CTaoiseach defends the Prime Minister
OL,4,Cfrom Trump's criticism at the White
OL,5,CHouse
OL,7,FHe said the relationship between
OL,8,FEurope and the US is "very, very
OL,9,Fimportant", and previous issues
OL,10,Fbetween the EU and the US last year,
OL,11,Fwhere the threat of a tariff war
OL,12,Floomed for months, had been resolved.
OL,14,F"I think we can get landing zone
OL,15,Fagain," Mr Martin said.
OL,17,F"Keir Starmer has done a lot to reset
OL,18,Fthe Irish-British relationship, I just
OL,19,Fwant to put that on the record.
OL,26,@pD@VOUqD@JO]vD@AOUwD@GO]yD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1773867709
OL,3,CTaoiseach defends the Prime Minister
OL,4,Cfrom Trump's criticism at the White
OL,5,CHouse
OL,7,F"But I do believe that he's a very
OL,8,Fearnest, sound person (which) you have
OL,9,Fa capacity to get on with, you've got
OL,10,Fon with him before.
OL,12,F"You've got on with other European
OL,13,Fleaders as well and I think you have
OL,14,Fthat capacity again."
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@AOUvD@UO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/12
